{
    "meta": {
        "instanceId": "277842713620d9f5554de3b1518b865a152c8c4db680008bd8aec536fc18b4a8"
    },
    "nodes": [
        {
            "id": "c0573700-e667-4fb3-ad1b-501c818e98ed",
            "name": "\ud83d\udcdd Note \u2014 Poll, Fetch & Deduplicate",
            "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
            "position": [
                1296,
                1072
            ],
            "parameters": {
                "color": 7,
                "width": 1276,
                "height": 836,
                "content": "### \u23f1\ufe0f Step 1 \u2014 Schedule Poll, Shopify Fetch & Deduplication\n**Schedule Trigger:** Runs every 10 minutes \u2014 no webhook needed, no Shopify app config required.\n**Shopify Node:** Fetches products published in the last 15 minutes using `published_at_min` filter and `status=active`.\n**Split In Batches:** Processes each new product one at a time to avoid API rate limits.\n**Airtable Search:** Looks up the product ID in the `ProductPostLog` table \u2014 if already found, the IF node skips it. Only truly new products proceed."
            },
            "typeVersion": 1
        },
        {
            "id": "a411ed24-de23-452d-80db-dbb1aac67f29",
            "name": "\ud83d\udcdd Note \u2014 Set, Upload & Switch Route",
            "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
            "position": [
                2624,
                960
            ],
            "parameters": {
                "color": 7,
                "width": 1068,
                "height": 964,
                "content": "### \ud83d\uddbc\ufe0f Step 2 \u2014 Data Prep, Image Upload & Platform Split\n**Set Node:** Maps and stores all product fields (title, price, URL, imageUrl, tags, vendor) into clean workflow variables \u2014 avoids repetitive expressions downstream.\n**HTTP Fetch + UploadToURL:** Downloads the product image binary, then uploads it to your CDN. The hosted URL is stored back via another Set node.\n**Switch Node:** Routes the enriched product data into 3 simultaneous branches \u2014 one each for Instagram, Facebook, and Twitter/X. Each branch is fully independent."
            },
            "typeVersion": 1
        },
        {
            "id": "8b6d17c6-a34c-46fe-ad14-0f279ce6e537",
            "name": "\ud83d\udcdd Note \u2014 3 Independent AI Caption Chains",
            "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
            "position": [
                3712,
                976
            ],
            "parameters": {
                "color": 7,
                "width": 444,
                "height": 948,
                "content": "### \ud83e\udd16 Step 3 \u2014 Per-Platform AI Caption Generation\n**3 Separate OpenAI Nodes:** Each platform branch has its own dedicated OpenAI chat call with a platform-specific system prompt.\n- **Instagram branch:** Emoji-rich, storytelling style, 10+ hashtags\n- **Facebook branch:** Conversational CTA-driven copy, link preview optimized\n- **Twitter/X branch:** Punchy under-260-char copy with price + link\nThis approach allows independent tuning of each platform's tone without shared parsing logic."
            },
            "typeVersion": 1
        },
        {
            "id": "5f12a735-089c-4f2a-aca2-9fbb5b61525c",
            "name": "\ud83d\udcdd Note \u2014 Post to Platforms & Log to Airtable",
            "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
            "position": [
                4192,
                976
            ],
            "parameters": {
                "color": 7,
                "width": 652,
                "height": 948,
                "content": "### \ud83d\udce4 Step 4 \u2014 Platform Posts & Airtable Result Log\n**Instagram:** Two-step Graph API flow (create container \u2192 publish). Container ID from step 1 is passed to step 2.\n**Facebook:** Graph API `/photos` endpoint posts image + caption to your Page.\n**Twitter/X:** Native Twitter node posts the punchy tweet.\n**Airtable \u2014 Log Results:** After all 3 posts, a final Airtable record is created/updated with `ProductID`, post statuses per platform, timestamp, and hosted image URL \u2014 prevents re-processing on next poll cycle."
            },
            "typeVersion": 1
        },
        {
