        {
            "id": "ac0f4384-9624-41b7-a4b0-1e59ce62c0fc",
            "name": "\ud83d\udccb MAIN \u2014 Workflow Overview1",
            "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
            "position": [
                432,
                336
            ],
            "parameters": {
                "width": 720,
                "height": 720,
                "content": "## \ud83d\udecd\ufe0f E-commerce Product Launch \u2014 Auto-Post to Instagram, Facebook & X\n\n**What this workflow does:**\nThis template polls your Shopify store every 10 minutes for newly published products. It checks Airtable to skip already-processed products (deduplication), fetches the product image, uploads it via UploadToURL, then routes each social platform through a Switch node \u2014 each getting its OWN dedicated AI caption generation via separate OpenAI message chains. Final posts go to Instagram (Graph API), Facebook Page, and Twitter/X, with results logged back to Airtable.\n\n**Architecture Highlights (structurally different from Template 1):**\n- \u23f1\ufe0f Schedule Trigger (polls Shopify every 10 min) \u2014 NOT a webhook\n- \ud83d\udd01 Split In Batches \u2014 processes multiple new products one by one\n- \ud83d\uddc3\ufe0f Airtable \u2014 deduplication log (checks + writes processed product IDs)\n- \ud83d\udd00 Switch Node \u2014 routes to 3 separate platform branches\n- \ud83e\udd16 3x Separate OpenAI calls \u2014 one per platform (Instagram / Facebook / Twitter)\n- \u2601\ufe0f UploadToURL \u2014 mandatory image CDN hosting\n- \ud83d\udcca Airtable \u2014 final post result logger\n\n**Setup Requirements:**\n1. Shopify API credentials (Admin API token with `read_products` scope)\n2. Airtable base with a table named `ProductPostLog` with fields: `ProductID`, `Title`, `PostedAt`, `InstagramStatus`, `FacebookStatus`, `TwitterStatus`, `ImageURL`\n3. OpenAI API credentials\n4. Facebook Graph API token (pages_manage_posts + instagram_content_publish)\n5. Twitter/X OAuth1 credentials\n6. UploadToURL endpoint in the upload node"
            },
            "typeVersion": 1
        },
        {
            "id": "8062fb1e-475e-43c3-9963-68a0d2feda42",
            "name": "HTTP \u2014 Fetch Product Image Binary1",
            "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
            "position": [
                2896,
                1456
            ],
            "parameters": {
                "url": "={{ $json.imageUrl }}",
                "options": {
                    "timeout": 20000,
                    "redirect": {
                        "redirect": {
                            "maxRedirects": 5
                        }
                    },
                    "response": {
                        "response": {
                            "responseFormat": "file"
                        }
                    }
                }
            },
            "typeVersion": 4.2
        },
        {
            "id": "007f354c-0bf9-4438-a24e-e6f4920e9f51",
            "name": "Instagram \u2014 Create Media Container1",
            "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
            "position": [
                4304,
                1312
            ],
            "parameters": {
                "url": "=https://graph.facebook.com/v19.0/YOUR_IG_ACCOUNT_ID/media",
                "method": "POST",
                "options": {
                    "timeout": 15000
                },
                "sendQuery": true,
                "queryParameters": {
                    "parameters": [
                        {
                            "name": "image_url",
                            "value": "={{ $('Set \u2014 Store Hosted Image URL').item.json.hostedImageUrl }}"
                        },
                        {
